[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Written evidence from [bold]Cycling Tynedale[bold] (CYS0012)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]There are already good guidelines promoting increased cycling and walking for both economic, health and welfare benefits. e.g. NICE guidelines PH8 and 41 are directed towards planners, highways agencies, etc. But in our area, Northumberland, the individual
[normal]s in power are either not aware of best practise or ignore it. 
[normal] Finances are a commonly held barrier to implementation of change, yet we have examples of considerable Highways spend where no consideration whatsoever was made to opportunistic inclusion of c
[normal]hanges to improve cycling
[normal]. 
