[normal]e.g. widespread recognition of need for safe, off road cycle route alon
[normal]g Tyne Valley, yet when A695, which follows this route, was resurfaced this year, no consideration of possible improvements for cyclists or pedestrians was made. This information was obtained under FOI. If improvements had been considered but rejected for 
[normal]particular reasons this would have been more understandable, so when the default response from local councilors is ‘no money’, that improvements were not even considered is immensely frustrating.
